Not one person is worthy, of Our Lord's Body and Blood.  All of us are sinners in thought and deed.  We pray this prayer before we partake of the Awesome Holy Mysteries because we know without Our Lord's Mercy in making us worthy, by His mercy, through no work or effort of our own, we would fry if we partook of the very flesh and blood of God himself.  We also hear <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong> Holy things for the Holy</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> and in which we sing <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>One is Holy One is the Lord</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.<br>
